    "content": "<p>\nThe <code>nsMsgViewSortOrder</code> interface contains constants used for sort direction in <a href=\"en/Thunderbird\">Thunderbird</a>. This interface isn't ever implemented. It is only used to store constants. For example to sort by date you would pass a function the value:\n</p>\n<pre class=\"eval\"> Components.interfaces.nsMsgViewSortOrder.ascending\n</pre>\n<p><br>\n</p><div style=\"border: solid #ddd 2px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n<div style=\"background: #eee; padding: 2px;\"><code><a href=\"https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/mailnews/base/public/nsIMsgDBView.idl\" rel=\"custom\">mailnews/base/public/nsIMsgDBView.idl</a></code><span style=\"text-align: right; float: right;\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Interfaces/About_Scriptable_Interfaces\" style=\"color: #00cc00; font-weight: 700;\">Scriptable</a></span></div>\n<span style=\"padding: 4px 2px;\">\n\n<i>Please add a summary to this article.</i>\n</span>\n\n<div style=\"background: #eee; padding: 2px;\">\n<span>Â </span>\n<span style=\"text-align: right; float: right;\">Last changed in Gecko 1.9 (Firefox 3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2 id=\"Constants\">Constants</h2>\n<table class=\"standard-table\"> <tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"header\">Name\n</td><td class=\"header\">Value\n</td><td class=\"header\">Description\n</td></tr> <tr>\n<td><code>none</code>\n</td><td>0\n</td><td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>ascending</code>\n</td><td>1\n</td><td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>descending </code>\n</td><td>2\n</td><td>\n</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>",
